        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">
            What is Know thyself?
          </a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>Welcome to an interactive web-application that allows us to know ourselves better.</p>
          <p>This application is based on the famous technique that <b>Jo</b>seph Luft and <b>Harri</b>ngton Ingham developed and called the 'Johari window'.
          The principle of the technique is that you select several adjectives from a pre-defined list that you believe they describe you.
          Then you ask several of your acquaintances to do the same and based on their answers, you can learn several things about yourself:</p>
          <table>
          <tr><td width="700">
          <ul>
            <li>Open arena: These are aspects of yourself that are both known to yourself and to the others</li>
            <li>Hidden or Facade: These are aspects that are known to you but not to the others</li>
            <li>Blind spot: These are aspects that are known to others but not to you</li>
            <li>Unknown: These are aspects that are neither know to you nor to others </li>
          </ul>
          <p>You can read more about the technique and research in the
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johari_window" target="_blank">Johari window</a> article on Wikipedia.</p>
          </td>
          <td>
          <p align="right"><img src="window.svg" height="200"></p>
          </td>
          </tr></table>
    
          <p>So, this is an online interactive version of a Johari window. But since it's a little bit different, I decided to give it
            the more poetic title of 'Know thyself' which is the translation of the ancient Greek 'Γνώθι σεαυτό'.
            'Γνώθι σεαυτό' was an aphorism given often by the Oracle of Delphi and <i>'is applied to those
              whose boasts exceed what they are.'</i> 
          <a href="http://www.stoa.org/sol-bin/search.pl?db=REAL&search_method=QUERY&login=
          guest&enlogin=guest&user_list=LIST&page_num=1&searchstr=gamma,333&field=adlerhw_gr&num_per_page=1" target="_blank">[1]</a></p>
          <p>I believe this application can help people better understand themselves and how others perceive them, which can allows
            one to boast less.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
